olive oil
2 Potato
1 Tomato
1 Cucumber
½ Lemon
1 packet Salmon
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Rocket leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water and add a generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat, until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and return to the pan.
• Add a drizzle of olive oil to potato and season with a pinch of salt. Toss to coat and lightly crush with a fork. Cover to keep warm.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the potato unpeeled.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato and cucumber. Zest lemon and slice into wedges.
• Pat salmon dry with paper towel. In a medium bowl, combine salmon, garlic & herb seasoning, a pinch of salt and pepper and a drizzle of olive oil. Set aside.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side.

TIP: Patting the skin dry helps it crisp up in the pan!

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, rocket leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• To the potatoes, add a squeeze of lemon juice and lemon zest, tossing to combine.

• Divide seared salmon, lemon crushed potatoes and rocket salad between plates.
• Top salmon with dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve. Enjoy!